item.title: Bank of America CEO Moynihan Says Credit Card Cap May Not Work as Expected
item.description: Bank of America CEO Brian Moynihan discusses the company's work with the White House to solve affordability issues for Americans. He says President Donald Trump's proposed 10% cap on credit card interest rates may have "an equal but opposite reaction." He speaks on "Bloomberg Surveillance" from the World Economic Forum in Davos. (Source: Bloomberg)
